To make a Google Cloud Run service unauthenticated, you need to adjust the authentication settings for your service. Here's how you can modify the code from the previous example to create an unauthenticated service:

```javascript
const { CloudRunServiceClient } = require('@google-cloud/run');

async function createUnauthenticatedCloudRunService() {
  const client = new CloudRunServiceClient();

  const location = 'us-central1'; // Replace with your desired location
  const serviceId = 'my-unauthenticated-cloud-run-service'; // Replace with your desired service ID
  const image = 'gcr.io/my-project/my-image'; // Replace with your Docker image URL

  const service = {
    apiVersion: 'serving.knative.dev/v1',
    kind: 'Service',
    metadata: {
      name: serviceId,
      namespace: 'default', // Replace with your desired namespace
    },
    spec: {
      template: {
        spec: {
          containers: [
            {
              image,
            },
          ],
        },
      },
      authentication: {
        anonymous: {},
      },
    },
  };

  const [operation] = await client.createService({
    parent: `namespaces/${location}`,
    serviceId,
    service,
  });

  console.log('Creating unauthenticated service...');
  await operation.promise();
  console.log('Unauthenticated service created!');
}

createUnauthenticatedCloudRunService().catch(console.error);
```

In this code, the `authentication` field is added to the `spec` section of the service definition. The `anonymous` setting under `authentication` makes the service unauthenticated, allowing anyone to access the service without requiring authentication.

Remember to adjust the values of `location`, `serviceId`, and `image` to match your project's requirements. As always, refer to the latest documentation for the most accurate and up-to-date information:

- Google Cloud Run Node.js Client Library: https://cloud.google.com/run/docs/reference/rest
- Google Cloud SDK: https://cloud.google.com/sdk
- Google Cloud Run Documentation: https://cloud.google.com/run/docs

